{
  "video_id": "rToBZSrxjgM",
  "title": "The nit-picking glory of The New Yorker's Comma Queen | Mary Norris",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13672.0,
      "end_time": 18846.0,
      "text": "I have spent the past 38 years trying to be invisible."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 19830.0,
      "end_time": 21258.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m a copy editor."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21807.0,
      "end_time": 23506.0,
      "text": "I work at The New Yorker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23531.0,
      "end_time": 27705.0,
      "text": "and copyediting for The New Yorker is like playing shortstop"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27729.0,
      "end_time": 29942.0,
      "text": "for a Major League Baseball team:"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29967.0,
      "end_time": 33379.0,
      "text": "every little movement gets picked over by the critics --"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33404.0,
      "end_time": 36600.0,
      "text": "God forbid you should commit an error."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 37860.0,
      "end_time": 41220.0,
      "text": "Just to clarify: copy editors don&#39;t choose what goes into the magazine."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 41530.0,
      "end_time": 43908.0,
      "text": "We work at the level of the sentence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 43932.0,
      "end_time": 45620.0,
      "text": "maybe the paragraph,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 45644.0,
      "end_time": 47722.0,
      "text": "the words, the punctuation."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 48175.0,
      "end_time": 50879.0,
      "text": "Our business is in the details."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 50904.0,
      "end_time": 56380.0,
      "text": "We put the diaeresis, the double dot, over the \"i\" in \"naïve.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 56591.0,
      "end_time": 58518.0,
      "text": "We impose house style."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 58542.0,
      "end_time": 61228.0,
      "text": "Every publication has a house style."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 61252.0,
      "end_time": 63775.0,
      "text": "The New Yorker&#39;s is particularly distinctive."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 64503.0,
      "end_time": 67283.0,
      "text": "We sometimes get teased for our style."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 67307.0,
      "end_time": 71647.0,
      "text": "Imagine -- we still spell \"teen-ager\" with a hyphen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 71671.0,
      "end_time": 73947.0,
      "text": "as if that word had just been coined."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 74919.0,
      "end_time": 78518.0,
      "text": "But you see that hyphen in \"teen-age\""
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 78543.0,
      "end_time": 81135.0,
      "text": "and that diaeresis over \"coöperate,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 81159.0,
      "end_time": 83161.0,
      "text": "and you know you&#39;re reading The New Yorker."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 83850.0,
      "end_time": 87348.0,
      "text": "Copyediting at The New Yorker is a mechanical process."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 87372.0,
      "end_time": 90571.0,
      "text": "There is a related role called query proofreading,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 90595.0,
      "end_time": 92451.0,
      "text": "or page-OK&#39;ing."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 92959.0,
      "end_time": 95729.0,
      "text": "Whereas copyediting is mechanical,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 95753.0,
      "end_time": 98228.0,
      "text": "query proofreading is interpretive."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 98696.0,
      "end_time": 102680.0,
      "text": "We make suggestions to the author through the editor"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 102920.0,
      "end_time": 104713.0,
      "text": "to improve the emphasis of a sentence"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 104737.0,
      "end_time": 107371.0,
      "text": "or point out unintentional repetitions"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 107395.0,
      "end_time": 111390.0,
      "text": "and supply compelling alternatives."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 112502.0,
      "end_time": 115479.0,
      "text": "Our purpose is to make the author look good."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 115504.0,
      "end_time": 118833.0,
      "text": "Note that we give our proofs not directly to the author,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 118857.0,
      "end_time": 120376.0,
      "text": "but to the editor."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 120400.0,
      "end_time": 124517.0,
      "text": "This often creates a good cop/bad cop dynamic"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 124541.0,
      "end_time": 128650.0,
      "text": "in which the copy editor -- I&#39;ll use that as an umbrella term --"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 128889.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131960.0,
      "text": "is invariably the bad cop."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 132800.0,
      "end_time": 134445.0,
      "text": "If we do our job well, we&#39;re invisible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 134469.0,
      "end_time": 136541.0,
      "text": "but as soon as we make a mistake,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 136565.0,
      "end_time": 140381.0,
      "text": "we copy editors become glaringly visible."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 141426.0,
      "end_time": 144957.0,
      "text": "Here is the most recent mistake that was laid at my door."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 145931.0,
      "end_time": 149455.0,
      "text": "[Last Tuesday, Sarah Palin, the pre-Trump embodiment"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 149479.0,
      "end_time": 152625.0,
      "text": "of populist no-nothingism in the Republican Party,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 152649.0,
      "end_time": 154960.0,
      "text": "endorsed Trump.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 154935.0,
      "end_time": 159143.0,
      "text": "\"Where were The New Yorker&#39;s fabled copy editors?\" a reader wrote."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 159167.0,
      "end_time": 162333.0,
      "text": "\"Didn&#39;t the writer mean &#39;know-nothingism&#39;?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 162789.0,
      "end_time": 164650.0,
      "text": "Ouch."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 164900.0,
      "end_time": 166762.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s no excuse for this mistake."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 166786.0,
      "end_time": 169875.0,
      "text": "But I like it: \"no-nothingism.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 169899.0,
      "end_time": 173857.0,
      "text": "It might be American vernacular for \"nihilism.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 173881.0,
      "end_time": 177880.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 177112.0,
      "end_time": 180136.0,
      "text": "Here, another reader quotes a passage from the magazine:"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 180160.0,
      "end_time": 184197.0,
      "text": "[Ruby was seventy-six, but she retained her authoritative bearing;"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 184221.0,
      "end_time": 188199.0,
      "text": "only her unsteady gait belied her age.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 188770.0,
      "end_time": 189921.0,
      "text": "He added:"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 189945.0,
      "end_time": 193280.0,
      "text": "\"Surely, someone at The New Yorker knows the meaning of &#39;belied,&#39;"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 193520.0,
      "end_time": 196260.0,
      "text": "and that it is the opposite of how it is used in this sentence."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 196284.0,
      "end_time": 197958.0,
      "text": "Come on! Get it together.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 198648.0,
      "end_time": 202156.0,
      "text": "Belie: to give a false impression."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 202180.0,
      "end_time": 204227.0,
      "text": "It should have been \"betrayed.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 205426.0,
      "end_time": 208301.0,
      "text": "E.B. White once wrote of commas in The New Yorker:"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 208325.0,
      "end_time": 213189.0,
      "text": "\"They fall with the precision of knives outlining a body.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 213213.0,
      "end_time": 214915.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 214939.0,
      "end_time": 217745.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s true -- we get a lot of complaints about commas."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 218124.0,
      "end_time": 222120.0,
      "text": "\"Are there really two commas in &#39;Martin Luther King, Jr., Boulevard&#39;?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 222746.0,
      "end_time": 227827.0,
      "text": "There may not be on the sign, but yes, that is New Yorker style for \"Jr.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 228192.0,
      "end_time": 230157.0,
      "text": "One wag wrote:"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 230181.0,
      "end_time": 233623.0,
      "text": "[\"Please, could you expel, or, at least, restrain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 233647.0,
      "end_time": 236671.0,
      "text": "the comma-maniac, on your editorial staff?\"]"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 236695.0,
      "end_time": 238470.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 238710.0,
      "end_time": 239222.0,
      "text": "Ah, well."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 239246.0,
      "end_time": 241490.0,
      "text": "In this case, those commas are well-placed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 241514.0,
      "end_time": 243385.0,
      "text": "except that there should not be one"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 243409.0,
      "end_time": 245411.0,
      "text": "between \"maniac\" and \"on.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 245435.0,
      "end_time": 246670.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 246694.0,
      "end_time": 250441.0,
      "text": "Also, if we must have commas around \"at least,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 250466.0,
      "end_time": 254506.0,
      "text": "we might change it up by using dashes around that phrase:"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 254530.0,
      "end_time": 257218.0,
      "text": "\"... -- or, at least, restrain --\""
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 258392.0,
      "end_time": 259562.0,
      "text": "Perfect."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 259586.0,
      "end_time": 261164.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 261188.0,
      "end_time": 262522.0,
      "text": "Then there&#39;s this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 262547.0,
      "end_time": 263985.0,
      "text": "\"Love you, love your magazine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 264900.0,
      "end_time": 269206.0,
      "text": "but can you please stop writing massive numbers as text?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 269230.0,
      "end_time": 270784.0,
      "text": "[two and a half million ...]"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 270808.0,
      "end_time": 271967.0,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 271991.0,
      "end_time": 274290.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 274530.0,
      "end_time": 277155.0,
      "text": "One last cri de coeur from a spelling stickler:"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 277179.0,
      "end_time": 282323.0,
      "text": "[\"Those long stringy things are vocal cords, not chords.\"]"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 282347.0,
      "end_time": 284496.0,
      "text": "The outraged reader added,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 284520.0,
      "end_time": 286353.0,
      "text": "\"I&#39;m sure I&#39;m not the first to write"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 286377.0,
      "end_time": 289598.0,
      "text": "regarding this egregious proofreading error,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 289622.0,
      "end_time": 292280.0,
      "text": "but I&#39;m equally sure I won&#39;t be the last."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 292520.0,
      "end_time": 293272.0,
      "text": "Fie!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 293296.0,
      "end_time": 295517.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 295541.0,
      "end_time": 297426.0,
      "text": "I used to like getting mail."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 299222.0,
      "end_time": 301818.0,
      "text": "There is a pact between writers and editors."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 301842.0,
      "end_time": 304221.0,
      "text": "The editor never sells out the writer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 304245.0,
      "end_time": 307797.0,
      "text": "never goes public about bad jokes that had to be cut"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 307821.0,
      "end_time": 310271.0,
      "text": "or stories that went on too long."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 310295.0,
      "end_time": 315153.0,
      "text": "A great editor saves a writer from her excesses."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 315558.0,
      "end_time": 317586.0,
      "text": "Copy editors, too, have a code;"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 317610.0,
      "end_time": 320930.0,
      "text": "we don&#39;t advertise our oversights."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 320593.0,
      "end_time": 323293.0,
      "text": "I feel disloyal divulging them here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 323317.0,
      "end_time": 326371.0,
      "text": "so let&#39;s have look at what we do right."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 327570.0,
      "end_time": 330474.0,
      "text": "Somehow, I&#39;ve gotten a reputation for sternness."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 331133.0,
      "end_time": 335250.0,
      "text": "But I work with writers who know how to have their way with me."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 335741.0,
      "end_time": 339889.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve known Ian Frazier, or \"Sandy,\" since the early 80s."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 339913.0,
      "end_time": 341542.0,
      "text": "And he&#39;s one of my favorites,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 341566.0,
      "end_time": 344100.0,
      "text": "even though he sometimes writes a sentence"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 344350.0,
      "end_time": 346131.0,
      "text": "that gives a copy editor pause."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 346846.0,
      "end_time": 349380.0,
      "text": "Here is one from a story about Staten Island"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 349404.0,
      "end_time": 351395.0,
      "text": "after Hurricane Sandy:"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 352920.0,
      "end_time": 356101.0,
      "text": "[A dock that had been broken in the middle and lost its other half"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 356125.0,
      "end_time": 358509.0,
      "text": "sloped down toward the water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 358533.0,
      "end_time": 362213.0,
      "text": "its support pipes and wires leaning forward"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 362237.0,
      "end_time": 366480.0,
      "text": "like when you open a box of linguine and it slides out.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 366720.0,
      "end_time": 367326.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 367350.0,
      "end_time": 372480.0,
      "text": "This would never have got past the grammarian in the days of yore."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 372504.0,
      "end_time": 373743.0,
      "text": "But what could I do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 373767.0,
      "end_time": 376371.0,
      "text": "Technically, the \"like\" should be an \"as,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 376395.0,
      "end_time": 377839.0,
      "text": "but it sounds ridiculous,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 377863.0,
      "end_time": 381576.0,
      "text": "as if the author were about to embark on an extended Homeric simile --"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 382211.0,
      "end_time": 385371.0,
      "text": "\"as when you open a box of linguine.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 385395.0,
      "end_time": 386704.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 386728.0,
      "end_time": 391504.0,
      "text": "I decided that the hurricane conferred poetic justice on Sandy"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 391528.0,
      "end_time": 393179.0,
      "text": "and let the sentence stand."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 393203.0,
      "end_time": 394289.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 394314.0,
      "end_time": 396322.0,
      "text": "Generally, if I think something is wrong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 396346.0,
      "end_time": 397838.0,
      "text": "I query it three times."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 397862.0,
      "end_time": 401717.0,
      "text": "I told Sandy that not long ago in a moment of indiscretion and he said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 401741.0,
      "end_time": 403252.0,
      "text": "\"Only three?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 403276.0,
      "end_time": 405200.0,
      "text": "So, he has learned to hold out."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 405440.0,
      "end_time": 407443.0,
      "text": "Recently, he wrote a story for \"Talk of the Town,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 407467.0,
      "end_time": 409688.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s the section at the front of the magazine"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 409712.0,
      "end_time": 412789.0,
      "text": "with short pieces on subjects ranging from Ricky Jay&#39;s exhibit"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 412814.0,
      "end_time": 414359.0,
      "text": "at the Metropolitan Museum"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 414383.0,
      "end_time": 417554.0,
      "text": "to the introduction of doggie bags in France."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 417578.0,
      "end_time": 419996.0,
      "text": "Sandy&#39;s story was about the return to the Bronx"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 420200.0,
      "end_time": 422686.0,
      "text": "of Supreme Court Justice Sonia Sotomayor."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 422711.0,
      "end_time": 425260.0,
      "text": "There were three things in it that I had to challenge."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 425284.0,
      "end_time": 426848.0,
      "text": "First, a grammar query."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 426872.0,
      "end_time": 429467.0,
      "text": "The justice was wearing black and Sandy wrote,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 429491.0,
      "end_time": 434567.0,
      "text": "[Her face and hands stood out like in an old, mostly dark painting.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 435430.0,
      "end_time": 436993.0,
      "text": "Now, unlike with the hurricane,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 437170.0,
      "end_time": 439485.0,
      "text": "with this \"like,\" the author didn&#39;t have the excuse"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 439509.0,
      "end_time": 441316.0,
      "text": "of describing hurricane damage."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 441340.0,
      "end_time": 445635.0,
      "text": "\"Like\" in this sense is a preposition, and a preposition takes an object,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 445660.0,
      "end_time": 446853.0,
      "text": "which is a noun."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 446877.0,
      "end_time": 449409.0,
      "text": "This \"like\" had to be an \"as.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 449433.0,
      "end_time": 452591.0,
      "text": "\"As in an old, mostly dark painting.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 452615.0,
      "end_time": 454265.0,
      "text": "Second, a spelling issue."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 454289.0,
      "end_time": 457284.0,
      "text": "The author was quoting someone who was assisting the justice:"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 457986.0,
      "end_time": 459408.0,
      "text": "[\"It will be just a minute."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 459432.0,
      "end_time": 462730.0,
      "text": "We are getting the justice mic&#39;ed,\"]"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 463434.0,
      "end_time": 464584.0,
      "text": "Mic&#39;ed?"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 464982.0,
      "end_time": 466979.0,
      "text": "The music industry spells it \"mic\""
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 467300.0,
      "end_time": 469361.0,
      "text": "because that&#39;s how it&#39;s spelled on the equipment."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 469385.0,
      "end_time": 471812.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d never seen it used as a verb with this spelling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 471836.0,
      "end_time": 474366.0,
      "text": "and I was distraught to think that \"mic&#39;ed\""
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 474390.0,
      "end_time": 476675.0,
      "text": "would get into the magazine on my watch."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 476699.0,
      "end_time": 477710.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 477734.0,
      "end_time": 481652.0,
      "text": "New Yorker style for \"microphone\" in its abbreviated form is \"mike.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 482519.0,
      "end_time": 485146.0,
      "text": "Finally, there was a sticky grammar and usage issue"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 485170.0,
      "end_time": 488884.0,
      "text": "in which the pronoun has to have the same grammatical number"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 488908.0,
      "end_time": 490359.0,
      "text": "as its antecedent."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 491292.0,
      "end_time": 494887.0,
      "text": "[everyone in the vicinity held their breath]"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 495491.0,
      "end_time": 499686.0,
      "text": "\"Their\" is plural and \"everyone,\" its antecedent, is singular."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 499710.0,
      "end_time": 502647.0,
      "text": "You would never say, \"Everyone were there.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 502672.0,
      "end_time": 506513.0,
      "text": "Everyone was there. Everyone is here."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 506537.0,
      "end_time": 510150.0,
      "text": "But people say things like, \"Everyone held their breath\" all the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 510175.0,
      "end_time": 511394.0,
      "text": "To give it legitimacy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 511418.0,
      "end_time": 514841.0,
      "text": "copy editors call it \"the singular &#39;their,&#39;\""
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 514865.0,
      "end_time": 517930.0,
      "text": "as if calling it singular makes it no longer plural."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 517953.0,
      "end_time": 519347.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 519371.0,
      "end_time": 524570.0,
      "text": "It is my job when I see it in print to do my best to eliminate it."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 525370.0,
      "end_time": 527848.0,
      "text": "I couldn&#39;t make it, \"Everyone held her breath,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 527872.0,
      "end_time": 529564.0,
      "text": "or \"Everyone held his breath,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 529588.0,
      "end_time": 532150.0,
      "text": "or \"Everyone held his or her breath.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 532174.0,
      "end_time": 534994.0,
      "text": "Whatever I suggested had to blend in."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 535180.0,
      "end_time": 536374.0,
      "text": "I asked, through the editor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 536398.0,
      "end_time": 538446.0,
      "text": "if the author would consider changing it"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 538470.0,
      "end_time": 541410.0,
      "text": "to \"All in the vicinity held their breath,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 541650.0,
      "end_time": 542907.0,
      "text": "because \"all\" is plural."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 542931.0,
      "end_time": 544880.0,
      "text": "Nope."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 544112.0,
      "end_time": 547342.0,
      "text": "I tried again: \"All those present held their breath?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 547366.0,
      "end_time": 549587.0,
      "text": "I thought this sounded vaguely judicial."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 549611.0,
      "end_time": 550858.0,
      "text": "But the editor pointed out"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 550882.0,
      "end_time": 553286.0,
      "text": "that we could not have \"present\" and \"presence\""
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 553311.0,
      "end_time": 554754.0,
      "text": "in the same sentence."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 555108.0,
      "end_time": 556686.0,
      "text": "When the final proof came back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 556711.0,
      "end_time": 559287.0,
      "text": "the author had accepted \"as\" for \"like,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 559311.0,
      "end_time": 561246.0,
      "text": "and \"miked\" for \"mic&#39;ed.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 561270.0,
      "end_time": 564744.0,
      "text": "But on \"Everyone held their breath,\" he stood his ground."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 565490.0,
      "end_time": 566886.0,
      "text": "Two out of three isn&#39;t bad."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 568100.0,
      "end_time": 569253.0,
      "text": "In the same issue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 569277.0,
      "end_time": 571799.0,
      "text": "in that piece on doggie bags in France,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 571823.0,
      "end_time": 575561.0,
      "text": "there was the gratuitous use of the f-word by a Frenchman."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 576260.0,
      "end_time": 578864.0,
      "text": "I wonder, when the mail comes in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 578888.0,
      "end_time": 581746.0,
      "text": "which will have offended the readers more."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 581770.0,
      "end_time": 583443.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 583467.0,
      "end_time": 584617.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 584642.0,
      "end_time": 587994.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}